.TH "_del_initiator_dep" 9 "_del_initiator_dep" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_del_initiator_dep \- allow @oh to smart-idle even if @init_oh is active
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" _del_initiator_dep
.BI "(struct omap_hwmod *oh "  ","
.BI "struct omap_hwmod *init_oh "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "oh" 12
struct omap_hwmod *
.IP "init_oh" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allow the hardware module \fIoh\fP to enter idle while the hardare
module initiator \fIinit_oh\fP is active.  Useful when a module will not
be accessed by a particular initiator (e.g., if a module will not
be accessed by the IVA, there should be no sleepdep between the IVA
initiator and the module).  Only applies to modules in smart-idle
mode.  If the clockdomain is marked as not needing autodeps, return
0 without doing anything.  Returns -EINVAL upon error or passes
along \fBclkdm_del_sleepdep\fP value upon success.
